# Slack MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the Slack MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Required Settings:
# -----------------
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN - Your Slack Bot User OAuth Token
#   Generate a token at: https://api.slack.com/apps > Your App > OAuth & Permissions
#   Required scopes: channels:history, channels:read, chat:write, reactions:write
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# CONTAINER_NAME - Name of the Docker container (default: slack-mcp-server)
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/slack:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
#
# Examples:
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-your-token-here
# CONTAINER_NAME=my-slack-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/slack:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=
# CONTAINER_NAME=slack-mcp-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/slack:latest
# RESTART_CLAUDE=true
